---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import RelatedLinks from "../components/RelatedLinks.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Getting a prescription — Mary Jane's Place"
  description="How to get a legal UK medical cannabis prescription, explained simply. We're not doctors — we point you to specialist clinics, unbiased and with no commission, and give prescribed patients a place to use their medicine legally."
>
  <section class="ph-top pad">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <div class="eyebrow kick rv">Prescriptions</div>
      <h1 class="rv">Getting a prescription.</h1>
      <p class="rv lede" style="margin-top:16px">
        How a legal UK medical cannabis prescription works. No GP referral needed to
        approach a specialist clinic. General guidance, not medical advice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <div class="card rv" style="background:var(--paper);border-left:4px solid var(--olive)">
        <div class="eyebrow">We're not doctors</div>
        <h2 class="rv" style="margin-top:8px;margin-bottom:10px">We point the way. We don't prescribe.</h2>
        <p>
          Only a registered specialist can assess you and prescribe. We don't — and won't.
          We explain the route and point you to UK specialist clinics: unbiased, no commission,
          no tie-ins. We lay out the options; you choose.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px">
          Once you're prescribed, Mary Jane's Place is the member space built around you — a
          safe, lawful place to use your medicine. We're building it now and growing it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow kick rv">How it works</div>
      <h2 class="rv">From first question to first dose.</h2>
      <div class="steps" style="margin-top:12px">
        <div class="step rv">
          <div class="n">STEP ONE</div>
          <h3>Check you might be eligible</h3>
          <p>
            Prescriptions are usually for adults with a diagnosed condition who have already
            tried other treatments without enough relief. It helps to gather your medical
            history before you start.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step rv">
          <div class="n">STEP TWO</div>
          <h3>Approach a specialist clinic</h3>
          <p>
            You can contact a UK specialist clinic directly — no GP referral needed. Ask us
            and we'll point you to the options so you can book your own assessment.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step rv">
          <div class="n">STEP THREE</div>
          <h3>Assessment &amp; prescription</h3>
          <p>
            A registered specialist reviews your case and, if it's clinically appropriate,
            issues a prescription. The decision sits entirely with them — eligibility is
            never guaranteed.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="step rv">
          <div class="n">STEP FOUR</div>
          <h3>Become a member &amp; use it with us</h3>
          <p>
            Once you're prescribed, <a class="tlink" href="/membership">join Mary Jane's Place</a>.
            Bring your medicine and use it
            legally in a space made for prescribed patients, with the equipment and people
            to help you get the most from it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow kick rv">Eligibility</div>
      <h2 class="rv">Who can usually be prescribed.</h2>
      <div class="info" style="margin-top:6px">
        <div class="info-block rv">
          <h3>Adults with a diagnosis</h3>
          <p>
            Prescriptions are generally for adults with a diagnosed condition. Common areas
            include chronic pain, anxiety, PTSD and several others — there's no fixed list.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-block rv">
          <h3>Other treatments tried</h3>
          <p>
            Specialists typically expect that you've already tried other treatments without
            adequate relief. Your medical history helps the clinic make that judgement.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-block rv">
          <h3>The specialist decides</h3>
          <p>
            Eligibility is a clinical decision made by a registered specialist on a
            case-by-case basis. Meeting the general criteria is not a guarantee of a
            prescription.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <div class="eyebrow kick rv">What to expect on cost</div>
      <h2 class="rv">A straight word on price.</h2>
      <p class="rv" style="max-width:66ch;margin-top:8px">
        Most UK prescriptions are private, and costs vary by clinic — assessment, follow-ups
        and the medicine. We can't quote a figure; it depends on your clinic and treatment.
        <!-- TODO: owner to confirm specifics -->
      </p>
      <p class="rv" style="max-width:66ch;margin-top:12px">
        Some clinics run access or discount schemes — for veterans, low incomes or students.
        Ask each clinic directly; we'll flag where it's worth looking.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow kick rv">No bias, ever</div>
      <h2 class="rv" style="margin-bottom:8px">Honest guidance, both ways.</h2>
      <p class="rv" style="max-width:66ch;margin-bottom:22px">
        We earn nothing from where you go or what you buy.
      </p>
      <div class="two">
        <div class="rv card" style="background:var(--paper);border-left:4px solid var(--olive)">
          <div class="eyebrow">Finding a clinic</div>
          <h3 style="margin-top:8px;margin-bottom:10px">Independent, no commission</h3>
          <p>
            Book your own assessment at a UK specialist clinic — no GP referral. No commission,
            no tie-ins, no steering. We lay out the options; you decide.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rv card" style="background:var(--paper);border-left:4px solid var(--olive)">
          <div class="eyebrow">Choosing a device</div>
          <h3 style="margin-top:8px;margin-bottom:10px">Recommended honestly</h3>
          <p>
            Same with equipment: honest advice on what suits your needs and budget, not what
            earns us most. Try one in the lounge first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rv" style="margin-top:20px;display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a class="btn" href="/membership">Become a member <span class="arr">→</span></a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/contact">Ask us about clinics</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/medical-cannabis">Medical cannabis, explained</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <div class="disc rv" style="margin-top:24px">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 8v5M12 16h.01"/></svg>
        <div>
          This page is general information and signposting only. It is <b>not medical advice</b>,
          and we are not doctors. Whether medical cannabis is right for you — and whether you
          can be prescribed it — is a decision for a qualified specialist. For your legal
          rights, see <a class="tlink" href="/your-rights">Your Rights</a>.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pad-sm" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <RelatedLinks items={[
        { href: "/medical-cannabis", label: "Medical cannabis, explained" },
        { href: "/membership", label: "Become a member" },
        { href: "/your-rights", label: "Your rights" },
        { href: "/contact", label: "Contact us" },
      ]} />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
